revision.text: {{Skip to talk}} {{Talk header|archives=yes|search=yes}} {{User:MiszaBot/config |archiveheader = {{talkarchivenav}} |maxarchivesize = 125K |counter = 4 |minthreadsleft = 3 |algo = old(100d) |archive = Talk:V-2 missile launch site, Blizna/Archive %(counter)d }} {{WikiProjectBannerShell|1= {{WikiProject Poland|class=B | b1 = yes | b2 = yes | b3 = yes | b4 = yes | b5 = yes | b6 = yes |importance=mid}} {{WPMILHIST|class=B | b1 = yes | b2 = yes | b3 = yes | b4 = yes | b5 = yes |Russian=yes|Polish=yes|German=y|Weaponry=yes|WWII=yes}} {{WikiProject Jewish history|class=B|importance=mid}} {{WikiProject Rocketry|class=B|importance=high}}}} == CE == Did quick ce while review pending, rv as desired, regards [[User:Keith-264|Keith-264]] ([[User talk:Keith-264|talk]]) 19:48, 4 November 2016 (UTC) :As a quick comment, there seems to be some over referencing as quite a few basic facts receive multiple references for no clear reason (eg, "An SS military base near Blizna was set up on 5 November 1943, from which 139 A4 (also known as V-2) rockets were launched for experimental purposes and for training.[3][11][5][6]", "worked at the Blizna test site and personally visited the test missile impact areas to troubleshoot any problems discovered during trials.[3][11][20][6][7][8][16]", etc). This makes the article look a bit dubious. Also, what makes "RussianSpaceWeb.Com" and "Polish Greatness.com" reliable sources that need to be used here? Some of the other references also seem to be enthusiast websites and the like. [[User:Nick-D|Nick-D]] ([[User talk:Nick-D|talk]]) 22:17, 4 November 2016 (UTC) :: {{U|Nick-D}} I added all the available references when putting the article together in the knowledge that we would loose a few. They all tell slightly different stories, so will be useful in the expansion of the article. Many refs are in Polish. As it is a new article I don't think the large amount of refs is doing it any harm. ::Best regards -- [[User:Marek69|Marek]].[[Special:Contributions/Marek69|69]] [[User_talk:Marek69|''talk'']] 16:31, 15 November 2016 (UTC) :Thank you {{U|Keith-264}} [[File:Face-smile.svg|21px]]-- [[User:Marek69|Marek]].[[Special:Contributions/Marek69|69]] [[User_talk:Marek69|''talk'']] 16:36, 15 November 2016 (UTC)
